Description_lang: Etched around the center of this orb of jade is a serpent eating its own tail.  Inscriptions on either hemisphere read: 'There is but one certainty - every end marks a new beginning.' This orb, carved during the reign of Pandaren Emperor Shu Blindeye in honor of the Jade Serpent, is a representation of her rebirth into a new body every hundred years. Yu'lon still bestows wisdom and insight from her temple in the Jade Forest.
